  "title": "Gustaf Heram's Arrival",
  "summary": "At New Alderaan's starport, the mysterious, aristocratic newcomer Gustaf disembarks a crowded passenger liner and settles into the Goodman's Tavern, where the veiled Brin, Dr. Lynae Cassius and her bodyguards, the Jedi Jessalyn, the Twi'lek Senator Alistair Al'Dira, and the pilot Ranma have also gathered. A spaceport quarantine over a Betarian blood worm traps them all inside just as a Rodian gunman opens fire on Gustaf, blasting his arm and crashing him into Brin. The tavern erupts into a firefight as two more thugs and then a second wave blow through the back wall, hurling grenades; Jessalyn deflects bolts and reverses a grenade with the Force but is knocked senseless, while Ranma carries her to safety up the stairs. The proud, paranoid Gustaf refuses help and tries to fight his own attackers, insisting the assassins are after him alone, until Lynae and her guards cut down the last gunmen with lethal precision. Law enforcement arrives too late to the cleared scene, and the wounded, near-fainting Gustaf is finally carried off to a hospital, with Brin and Alistair left to wonder who wanted him dead.",
